latestPosts.caption:
May Allah swt accept from us تَقَبَّلَ اللهُ مِنَّا وَمِنكُم
Hajj Mubarak to my fellow brothers & sisters who took upon this sacred journey with us this year & Eid Mubarak to everyone celebrating. 🫶🏻✨

Where do I begin? I’m out of words as I put my thoughts & feelings together about this blessed experience. Truly so grateful to be amongst the chosen ones this year (may Allah swt call us to his home again, allahumaAmeen). I’ve only ever heard Hajj being a Journey of a lifetime but to able to perform it with your spouse is in itself a soulful experience. Alhamdulillah for a partner who pushes me to be better everyday, not just in terms of dunya but also in matters that concern our hereafter. Without his patience my Hajj journey wouldn’t be what it was. Hajj requires SO much patience & restraint that I wasn’t entirely ready. But our lord is so great that he showed up for us in unimaginable ways. We decided that being young & achieving this milestone was a priority for us, everything else can wait & subhanAllah things worked out in our favor. 🥺
I take this as another chance at life, to be better a better person overall, may Allah swt make it easy for me. If you knew me before Hajj, you didn’t know me at all. That’s how I want to be, to be able to take this opportunity that the Almighty has given me to achieve some personal goals that i’ve set for myself. Please make dua that I am steadfast upon those goals. In sha Allah this Hajj changes us for the better. 🤍

#hajj #hajji #hajj2025 #hajjmubarak #eidmubarak #mecca #makkahalmukarramah

latestPosts.caption:
Transport to the golden empires of Peru @australianmuseum 🇵🇪

This immersive experience with thousands of years of history was nothing sort of a mini getaway straight to the mountains of Machu Picchu. The 360 degree VR experience has to be my favorite part, with not only fantastic visuals, but this educational experience makes you feel like you’re floating through the breathtaking mountains of Machu Pichu. So impressive!
Over 130 ancient artifacts from one of the world’s most captivating civilization & an impressive gold collection with so many interactive elements throughout the experience. You cannot miss!

One last weekend before the “Machu Picchu” exhibit wraps up, you can book your tickets via @australianmuseum 🇦🇺
